-- Kenyan Stock Trading Starts in Nairobi After Delay Due to Software Problem
-- Sarah McGregor
-- 2010-07-12T08:17:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/kenyan-stock-trading-starts-in-nairobi-after-delay-due-to-software-problem.html

          
          
             Trading on the Nairobi Stock
Exchange began more than an hour late after a software problem
with the automated bidding system prevented users from logging
in, Information Technology Manager David Waggema said.  
 Trading started at 10:50 a.m. local time, compared to its
usual 9:30 a.m. commencement, after the technical glitch was
fixed, said Waggema by phone from Kenyaâ€™s capital Nairobi today.  
